Repost from @abc7chicago
•
Residents in Woodridge and Naperville woke up to widespread destruction after a tornado ripped through the area overnight Sunday. An EF-3 Tornado touched down packing winds up to 140 mph. 

The tornado began in Naperville before it moved into Woodridge. Woodridge police said the tornado touched down east of Route 53 between 83rd Street and 75th Street. The tornado then traveled east to the Lemont Road area.

The tornado then moved into the Darien and Burr Ridge area. ABC7 Meteorologist Tracy Butler said the tornado could have traveled as many as 15 miles.

At least 75 homes in the suburb were damaged, including one home had the entire second story missing, while others had damage to roofs and garages.

What are those?! #nike #af1 #nikeairforce1 @nike @airforce1nike @englishsole #notanad just love them! 
@goodnightjb 
.

The Women’s Nike Air Force 1 Low “UV Reactive” is a women’s exclusive look for the retro basketball shoe that features photochromic inks that give the shoe a new multicolor look when exposed to UV light. It appears as a variation of the Air Force 1’s “White on White” colorway when not in contact with UV rays. When exposed, the forefoot, eyelets, mid-panel, collar, and heel adjust into various shades of pastel colors. Specifically, the perforated toe and mid-panel turn yellow while the forefoot, eyelets, collar, and Swoosh transition from white to light blue, purple, and pink, respectively. A white midsole is paired with an icy translucent blue outsole. A Silicone Swoosh hang tag accompanies the shoe.
